Then $h = AD = b \sin C = c \sin B,$ so
\[AD^2 = b^2 \sin^2 C = c^2 \sin^2 B.\]Then
\[\frac{AD^2}{bc} = \frac{b \sin C}{c} \cdot \frac{c \sin B}{b} = \sin B \sin C = \frac{1}{2} (\cos (B - C) - \cos A).\]Hence,
\[AD^2 = \frac{bc}{2} (\cos (B - C) - \cos A) = 10 \cdot \frac{31}{32} - 2 \cdot \frac{1}{2} (\cos A),\]so $\cos A = \frac{5 - 16 \cos (B - C)}{8} = -\frac{3}{8}.$  Then
\[a^2 = 41 - 40 \cdot (-\frac{3}{8}) = \frac{329}{2},\]so $a = \boxed{\sqrt{\frac{329}{2}}}.$

