Then $\mathbf{v} - \operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{n}} \mathbf{v}$ is a vector in plane $P.$  Therefore, the reflection of $\mathbf{v}$ through plane $P$ is given by
\[\mathbf{r} = \mathbf{v} - 2 \operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{n}} \mathbf{v} = \mathbf{v} - 2 \frac{\mathbf{v} \cdot \mathbf{n}}{\|\mathbf{n}\|^2} \mathbf{n}.\]Let $\mathbf{v} = \begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \\ z \end{pmatrix}.$  Then
\[\mathbf{v} \cdot \mathbf{n} = x + y - z.\]Also, $\|\mathbf{n}\| = \sqrt{3},$ so
\[\operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{n}} \mathbf{v} = \frac{\mathbf{v} \cdot \mathbf{n}}{\|\mathbf{n}\|^2} \mathbf{n} = \frac{1}{3} \begin{pmatrix} x + y - z \\ x + y - z \\ -x - y + z \end{pmatrix}.\]Therefore,
\begin{align*}
\mathbf{r} &= \begin{pmatrix} x \\ y \\ z \end{pmatrix} - 2 \cdot \frac{1}{3} \begin{pmatrix} x + y - z \\ x + y - z \\ -x - y + z \end{pmatrix} \\
&= \begin{pmatrix} -\frac{1}{3} x + \frac{2}{3} y + \frac{2}{3} z \\ \frac{2}{3} x - \frac{1}{3} y + \frac{2}{3} z \\ \frac{2}{3} x + \frac{2}{3} y - \frac{1}{3} z \end{pmatrix}.
\end{align*}Hence,
\[\mathbf{R} = \boxed{\begin{pmatrix} -\frac{1}{3} & \frac{2}{3} & \frac{2}{3} \\ \frac{2}{3} & -\frac{1}{3} & \frac{2}{3} \\ \frac{2}{3} & \frac{2}{3} & -\frac{1}{3} \end{pmatrix}}.\]

