Then $\mathbf{r}$ is the projection of $\mathbf{v}$ onto plane $P,$ followed by a reflection across plane $P.$  The projection of $\mathbf{v}$ onto plane $P$ is given by
\[\operatorname{proj}_{\mathbf{n}} \mathbf{v} = \frac{\mathbf{v} \cdot \mathbf{n}}{\|\mathbf{n}\|^2} \mathbf{n} = \frac{\mathbf{v} \cdot \mathbf{n}}{3} \begin{pmatrix} 1 \\ 1 \\ -1 \end{pmatrix}.\]Then
